title: Check Out Kodak Black's New Music Video for "Tunnel Vision" | Complex
text:
Check Out Kodak Black's New Music Video for "Tunnel Vision" By Gavin Evans Gavin Evans is a contributor for Complex Media.
Feb 16, 2017 Share Tweet Subscribe to Complex Video via Kodak Black Lately Kodak Black's been in the news for reasons that are--shall we say--not good at all (examples include his beef with Hurricane Chris , broadcasting sex from his hotel room , a challenge to fight Lil Wayne , his haircut getting roasted, and especially his pending sexual assault case ). For that long (and still abbreviated) list of reasons it's nice to see him back in the headlines for, you know, his actual music.
On Thursday his entire video for Tunnel Vision , produced by Metro Boomin and Southside, came out. As you can probably tell from a certain hat that you may've seen on the heads of some senior citizens in Florida, he's not exactly trying to win over the Trump crowd with this release.
Related The 'Cash Me Ousside' Girl Didn't Get Paid for That Kodak Black Video (UPDATE) Kodak Black Shades Hurricane Chris While Chilling in His Swimming Pool Kodak Black Broadcasts Hotel Room Sex on IG Live, Gets Dragged The video was previously teased from his Instagram account last December.
In case you're wondering what his immediate future holds, he'll also be one of the many performers on the upcoming Nobody Safe Tour , which will run from May 4-June 30. Other artists on said tour will include Future, Migos, Tory Lanez, Young Thug and ASAP Ferg. You can check out if and when that show is stopping anywhere near you right here .
Tickets will be on sale for it on Friday.
